I"ý<h2 id="standard-buttons">Standard Buttons</h2>

<p>Use the standard button styles to convey the most important action on you want the users to take. For actions outside of the top two actions, use the <a href="#other-buttons">other buttons</a>. See the <a href="https://v2.designsystem.digital.gov/components/button/">USWDS Button Usage</a> for more on how to use buttons.</p>

<p>Note: the  vertical alignment of a button is governed by the <a href="/layout">layout grid</a>.</p>

<h5 id="primary">Primary</h5>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">&lt;button</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"usa-button"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><button class="usa-button">Default</button>
<button class="usa-button usa-button--hover">Hover</button>
<button class="usa-button usa-button--active">Active</button>
<button class="usa-button usa-focus">Focus</button>
<button class="usa-button" disabled="">Disabled</button></p>

<h5 id="secondary">Secondary</h5>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">&lt;button</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"usa-button usa-button--outline"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
